<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1922-08-24T05:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1922-08-24T05:00:00-05:00" n="740" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d740">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">861.77/2657: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Harvey</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-08-24T11:00:00+01:00"><hi rend="italic">August 24,
                                        1922—11 a.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received August 24—8:44
                                a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>372. Your telegram 246 of August 11, 6 p.m.<note n="83" xml:id="d740fn83">Not printed; see telegram no. 87, Aug. 11, to the Ambassador in
                                Japan, <ref target="#pg_910">p. 910</ref>.</note> I am formally
                            advised that His Majesty’s Government concur in the course of action
                            proposed in the memorandum transmitted by your telegram 209 of July 17,
                            3 p.m.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Harvey</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>